# AGENTS.md — stt-long-transcription
# MbanzaNLP · Kinyarwanda ASR Service · DinoSoft Engineering Standards
# Codex: read this file completely before touching any code.

## 1. What This Repository Is

This is the MbanzaNLP Kinyarwanda Speech-to-Text service. It is a Gradio application
deployed on a Hugging Face free CPU Space that transcribes Kinyarwanda audio files
using the Wav2Vec2-BERT 2.0 model fine-tuned on 1,000 hours of Kinyarwanda speech
(checkpoint: `badrex/w2v-bert-2.0-kinyarwanda-asr-1000h`).

The system is specifically architected for a free-tier Hugging Face Space, which means:
- The Space's disk is ephemeral and is lost on every restart or configuration change.
- The only durable storage is the HF Dataset repository (`mbaza-nlp/stt-job-state`).
- The Space has no SLA, no guaranteed uptime, and restarts without warning.

Every architectural decision in this codebase flows from those three facts.


## 2. The Single Most Important Design Principle

Read this once and never violate it:

> **The Space only processes. The dataset repo owns durable state.
> The Space maintains a volatile in-memory cache for live UI rendering only.**

This means:
- `state/job_store.py` is the ONLY module that calls the HF Hub API.
- `state/cache.py` is a volatile dict. It is NEVER the source of truth.
- `app.py` reads from `cache.py` only. It NEVER reads from the Hub directly.
- The UI polls `cache.py` every 5 seconds. It NEVER polls the Hub.
- Every durable write goes through `job_store.py` with backoff on HTTP 429.

If you are about to write code that reads from the Hub in any module other than
`state/job_store.py`, stop and reconsider. You are violating the architecture.

