## 6. The Admission Controller — Critical Usage Rule

The `AdmissionController` in `scheduler/admission.py` uses `asyncio.Semaphore`.
When you call `admission.acquire()`, you MUST call `admission.release(slot)` in a
`finally` block. Failure to do this will leak a slot and permanently reduce concurrency.

The correct pattern in every caller is:

```python
slot = await _admission.acquire(duration_secs=duration)
try:
    # ... all processing ...
finally:
    _admission.release(slot)
```

Never call `release()` only in the happy path. The `finally` block is not optional.

