## 7. State Transition Rules

A job record transitions through four statuses: `queued` → `processing` → `complete`
or `failed`. The rules for when each transition happens are strict:

- Set `queued` when the job is created in `job_store.create_job()`. This is the
  only place where a new job record is born.
- Set `processing` when the first `job_store.update_job_chunk()` write succeeds.
  The first chunk write triggers this transition automatically inside `job_store.py`.
- Set `complete` only after `inference/postprocess.stitch_chunks()` has run and
  returned a non-empty string. Call `job_store.complete_job()` immediately after.
- Set `failed` on any unhandled exception inside the transcription loop. Call
  `job_store.fail_job(job_id, reason=str(e))` in the except block. Always include
  the job ID in the user-facing error message returned from `app.py`.

After every call to `job_store.*`, immediately call `cache.put(job_id, record)` to
keep the volatile read model in sync. This is the only way the UI sees updates.

