## 10. Test Requirements

Write the test before writing the implementation. This is not a preference — it is
the required workflow. Every task in the implementation plan follows this order:
write failing test → run to confirm failure → implement → run to confirm pass → commit.

Every test must be deterministic. Do not write tests that depend on network calls,
real model inference, or wall clock time. Mock the Hub API in all `job_store` tests.
Mock the model and processor in all decoder tests.

Test names must describe the behaviour under test in plain English, not the function
name. Write `test_short_job_acquires_priority_slot`, not `test_acquire`.

The CI pipeline will fail if coverage of `inference/` and `state/` packages drops
below 80%. Check coverage before committing with:

```bash
pytest tests/ --cov=inference --cov=state --cov-report=term-missing
```

