## 11. WER Regression Gate

The file `wer_baseline.json` in the repository root records the last known-good WER
for the model checkpoint named in `config.MODEL_NAME`. The CI pipeline measures WER
against the Common Voice Kinyarwanda test split after every passing test run and
blocks deployment if any domain's WER regresses by more than 2 percentage points
absolute above the baseline value.

Do not edit `wer_baseline.json` manually. It is updated only by the CI pipeline's
`scripts/measure_wer.py` script after a validated deployment. If you believe the
baseline is wrong, open a PR and justify the change in the PR description.

