## 13. What Not to Do

The following patterns are explicitly banned. If you encounter them in existing code,
flag them as part of your task before touching anything else.

Do not call the Hub API from `app.py`, `cache.py`, or any `inference/` module. Only
`state/job_store.py` may call the Hub.

Do not use file size as a scheduling or duration signal. Only `torchaudio.info()` duration.

Do not call `admission.release()` outside a `finally` block.

Do not hardcode constants. Everything numeric goes in `config.py` first.

Do not write to disk outside of the temporary directory provided to `chunk_audio()`.
The Space's ephemeral disk must not be treated as persistent storage for any purpose.

Do not catch bare `Exception` without re-raising or logging with the full context
(job ID, file path, chunk index). Silent failures that produce no diagnostic information
are worse than crashes because they are invisible.

Do not add synchronous blocking calls to the Gradio event loop without wrapping them
in `asyncio.to_thread()`. Long blocking calls in the event loop freeze the UI for
every connected user simultaneously.

