## 14. Environment Variables Required

Set these as Hugging Face Space secrets before deployment. The app will not function
without them.

`HF_TOKEN` — A Hugging Face token with write access to the `mbaza-nlp/stt-job-state`
dataset repository. This is used by `state/job_store.py` for all Hub reads and writes.

No other secrets are required. The model checkpoint is loaded publicly via the
`transformers` library without authentication.

---

## 15. Startup Sequence

When the Space starts, `app.py` executes these steps at module import time in this
order: (1) call `job_store.load_all_jobs()` to pull the full jobs JSON from the Hub,
(2) call `cache.seed_from_store()` to populate the volatile read model, (3) create
the singleton `AdmissionController`. If step 1 fails because the Hub is unreachable
at startup, the cache starts empty and the system continues — existing jobs will not
be recovered in this session, but new jobs can still be processed.
